The{ Warner} family founded a tile works in Star Lane, Knowl Hill, over 100 years ago. Houses for their workers were built, using tiles produced at the factory, on the Bath Road. These are now privately owned. The business stayed in the family until {March 1985} when it was bought by {IBSTOCK BUILDING PRODUCTS.}
The new company is to be called { IBSTOCK WARNER LTD} The business is valued at Â£5.5 million and has an annual turnover of Â£1.5m.
Ibstock produces facing bricks at its other works. It is intended to increase production at the Star Lane works and re-introduce some of the old techniques in the production of more complicated tiles. Some new equipment will be computer controlled.
